Ukraine’s Gross External Debt Rises on Eurobond, Corporate Loans

-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 
2011-03-21T16:36:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/ukraine-s-gross-external-debt-rises-on-eurobond-corporate-loans.html
Ukraine’s gross external debt
jumped 5.12 percent in the fourth quarter as the country sold
Eurobonds and private companies borrowed, the central bank said.  The debt totaled $117.3 billion as of Jan. 1, compared with
$111.6 billion as of Oct. 1, the Kiev-based  Natsionalnyi Bank
Ukrainy  said today in a statement on its website.  State foreign debt jumped to $25 billion through the
end of December, compared with $23.6 billion at the end of the
previous quarter, the bank said. Private companies’ debt rose to
$50.8 billion, compared with $47.6 billion at the end of the
third quarter, the data shows.  Gross external debt jumped 13.5 percent in all of 2010, the
bank said. Of the total debt, 70.4 percent was denominated in
dollars and 10.7 percent in euros.  External debt due within the next 12 months totaled
$47.3 billion, the data showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
